features: Bulk Pack of 10 Multi Color Headphones, with each headphone individually packaged. Includes 10 Colors; Red, Pink, Blue, Black, Green, Purple, Orange, Yellow, Gray, White. Providing a variety of options to suit different preferences or organizational needs.

On-ear headphones ensure a comfortable listening experience throughout the day without fatigue or soreness. The soft foam cushions minimize sound leakage, reduce noise and improve the fidelity of music.

Retractable headband ensures optimal fitting, making sure they fit just right. Whether you're a kid, a teenager, or an adult, you can easily adjust the band fit to suit your head size. Headphones feature 90 Degree swivel ear cup for easy placement and storage.

There is NO microphone, remote or volume control on these headphones. Suitable for airplane travel, school classrooms, study areas, Co-working spaces, library, museums, language learning and standardized testing experiences for all ages.

4-foot cord is suitable for most uses; 3.5mm right-angle plug will connect with all standard audio jacks and resists accidental pull-out. Compatible with iPhone, iPad, Chromebook, Laptop, PC, Android tablets, MP3 players, CD players, fitness equipment, and other devices.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Inexpensive but effective
reviews.reviewText: These little, inexpensive headphone have great sound. I bought a multipack so I could have them at work, home, my car, and travel bag. They are, of course, no match for professional grade headphones, the sound quality is really excellent. I can't wear earpods because they fall out of my ears constantly. This is the next best thing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great product at great price
reviews.reviewText: Ordered for classroom use. Kids like the colors and sonically, they do the trick. Have held up really well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good for kids for school
reviews.reviewText: Needed just for school when you don't want to spend a lot on headphones that you know will probably not last long with kid handling. Other than that, it sound clear and to get them in a multipack should last for my homeschool kiddos. Even if they do break, not to be upset. I spent $15 to $20 on headphones per kid that didn't last. Lesson learned.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Fine for classroom
reviews.reviewText: These work just fine for my middle school classroom. They do get used a lot by my students. I bought them in September, and I just threw out the first pair that broke (no sound, only static). I tell my students to treat these expensive, cheap headphones kindly so they last a little longer.I'm satisfied with them and how much use my students get out of them. I do wish they were better quality but they are a pretty good price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best headsets I have every had.
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a set of headsets that are not only comfortable to wear on my VERY WIDE head, but give wonderful sound quality. These headsets do not press excessively into your ears. No discomfort.These headsets not only give good stereo sound, but allow you to carry on a conversation with a person next to you at the same time.Easiest 5 star I have ever given.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Don't Buy Cheap and Expect Quality
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this product because over the years of buying the wire earphones which broke and frayed all of the time, I thought a headset would not have this problem. However, I should have invested in a more expensive headset. This headset was not worth purchasing. The headset part is very hard and uncomfortable. The ear pods have very little padding (only foam). So they were uncomfortable also. The sound was low quality but acceptable, I only used for my small tablet. The lesson to myself will be to pay more to get a better product. You do get what you paid for, and in this case a cheaply made product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These work as well as any other I've ever tried. And the price per unit is even more attractive. I bought these MANY months ago, and have only had to get rid of one. And that was due to my leaving it on the floor where the cats and dog made it a play toy. 😁

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for students
reviews.reviewText: As a high school teacher, students cannot play music through their computers during class. These headphones work good for assignments that require audio and we don't have 20+ students with their volume maxed anymore.

Head phones were as described, Iam VERY hard on head phones as I use them to fall asleep every night and usually go through a set every few weeks! That’s why I usually purchase cheaper ones, I am still on the very first set since I purchased them! ( over a month so far) the only downside of them are they are a bit big, even for my big head, I had to cut a piece of pool noodle to use as a spacer so they wouldn’t keep falling off my grandson’s head ( it works) Other than that, the sound is actually not bad at all,and they come in a wide variety of colours so everyone can pick their own colour, would definitely purchase again, but Iam guessing these will last the rest of MY LIFE!
